8a89c290-727b-494c-9d6b-eec2cf45af4d.0761edc6-d8c5-44e6-a03a-a46ad5fa6d99.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
8a89c290-727b-494c-9d6b-eec2cf45af4d.11014736-7f83-43f0-869e-8fa7afdc7f4c.description=
This is an operation that does nothing, and can be used to display information to the user by editing the display tab. It can also be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs, and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.

8a89c290-727b-494c-9d6b-eec2cf45af4d.description=
Synopsis

    This flow sets the default gateway for a vServer based on the IP address.
    setVserverDefaultGatewayByIp performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the net interfaces of the IP.
      2. Using the net inteface information, find the rounting group.
      3. Create a net routing group based on the found routing group.
      4. Pass the information back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer used in the flow (required).
    ipAddress - The IP address of the LIF (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    defaultGateway - The default gateway connection set up for the vServer (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    metric - 

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case a default gateway for a vServer.  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.
    Duplicate - This vServer already has a default gateway.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
flow.name: setVserverDefaultGatewayByIp

staticBinding.value: setVserverDefaultGatewayByIp: INFO: set defaultGateway=${defaultGateway} for ipAddress=${ipAddress}
setVserverDefaultGatewayByIp: INFO: check routingGroup=${routingGroup} for ipAddress=${ipAddress}
